N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 17 ยง 35.4 - Incorporation by reference

State Regulations

The provisions of the Federal Register which have been
incorporated by reference in this Part have been filed in the Office of the

Secretary of State of the State of New York, the publication so filed being the
booklet entitled: Federal Register, volume 64, number 21, 49 CFR part
26, dated

February 2, 1999, published by the United States Government Printing Office. The regulations incorporated by reference may be examined at the Office of the

Department of State, 41 State Street, Albany, NY 12231, at the libraries of the

New York Supreme Court, the State of New York Legislative Library, the New York

State Department of Transportation, Office of Legal Affairs or Office of Equal

Opportunity Development and Compliance, State Office Campus, Albany, NY 12232. They also may be purchased from the Superintendent of Documents, Government

Printing Office, Washington, DC 20402. Copies of the Federal Register are also
available at many public libraries and bar association
libraries. Notes
